                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2974: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-07T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 7, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 9—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>641. The Secretariat has circulated a telegram dated December 6 from the Emperor
                    of Abyssinia protesting against indiscriminate Italian air bombardments. The
                    Emperor stated that the bombardment of Dessie on December 6 “was established by
                    four Red Cross doctors namely Doctors Dassius, Loeb, Schuppler and Bellot and by
                    the representatives of the Associated Press, the <hi rend="italic">Times</hi>,
                    Reuter, <hi rend="italic">Chicago Tribune</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Daily
                        Express”</hi> He added, “We have ourselves established the death of a
                    tourist and of two children; and the American Hospital of Dessie, which carries
                    with authorization the markings of the Red Cross, has been seriously
                    damaged.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
